вҖ»вҖ»
# scaffold-sky-workflow

Manually-run meta-workflow that authors a brand-new `.sky` workflow from a
plain-English brief, then lints it until it passes. Flow:

  (manual run: --var dir, name, request)
       в”Ӯ
       в–ј
   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ   writes from {{request}}   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ
   в”Ӯ author в”Ӯ в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–¶ в”Ӯ <dir>/<name>/workflow.sky в”Ӯ
   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   (sky-workflow-authoring)  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ
       в”Ӯ                                          в–І
       в–ј                                          в”Ӯ edits to fix errors
   в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ                                     в”Ӯ
   в”Ӯ  lint  в”Ӯ в”Җв”Җв”Җ skyway lint в”Җв”Җв–¶ errors? в”Җв”Җyesв”Җв”Җв–¶ fixв”ҳ   (loop, max 6 passes)
   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                     в”Ӯ
                                  no (clean)
                                   в”Ӯ
                                   в–ј
                                 done

Run it (you choose where the file lands with --var dir):

  skyway run scaffold-sky-workflow \
    --var dir=".sky/workflows" \
    --var name="deploy-on-tag" \
    --var request="on a GitHub release, run the deploy script and post the result to Slack"

  - dir     directory the file is written to вҖ” STATE THIS before running (e.g. .sky/workflows)
  - name    kebab-case directory name (generates <dir>/<name>/workflow.sky)
  - request what the workflow should do, in plain English

Language: the brief in {{request}} may be in any language. The generated
workflow is always written in English (name, keys, node ids, prompt bodies);
only the вҖ»вҖ» comment blocks may be in the brief's language.

Required skill вҖ” install before first run (no marketplace plugin needed):

  skyway library install sky-workflow-authoring
вҖ»вҖ»

вҠ•metaвҠ•
name = "scaffold-sky-workflow"
description = "Author a new .sky workflow from a plain-English brief and lint it until clean. Fire via: skyway run scaffold-sky-workflow --var dir=<dir> --var name=<file> --var request=<what it should do>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
max_budget_usd = 2.00
ui = "ui/workflow"
вҠ•вҠ•

вҖ»authorвҖ»
Step 1 вҖ” author. Writes the new workflow file from the brief ({{request}}) via the
sky-workflow-authoring skill. Outputs {{dir}}/{{name}}/workflow.sky. No edges.
вҖ»вҖ»

В§authorВ§
model = "sonnet"
skills = ["sky-workflow-authoring"]
ui = "ui/author"
В§В§

вҲҶauthorвҲҶ
Author a new Skylence `.sky` workflow at {{dir}}/{{name}}/workflow.sky.

What it must do: {{request}}

Language rule: the brief above may be written in any language. Write the workflow itself entirely in English вҖ” `name`, all config keys, node ids, and every вҲҶ prompt body. Only the вҖ»вҖ» comment blocks may be written in the brief's language, to document the workflow for its author.

Follow the sky-workflow-authoring skill exactly: the four Unicode delimiter blocks (вҠ•metaвҠ•, В§idВ§, вҲҶidвҲҶ, вҖ»вҖ»), `name = "{{name}}"` matching the filename, exactly one trigger, and a sensible node DAG. Pick node types (claude / bash / script / http / loop) that fit the brief. Two audiences (per the skill): write the вҲҶ prompt bodies for the model (terse, machine-oriented, no concern for human readability); write the вҖ»вҖ» comment blocks for the human (clear, and when the flow branches/loops/gates add the diagram that explains it fastest: ASCII, Mermaid, sequence, or swimlane). Create the {{dir}} directory if absent.

File editing rule: if `skylence_read` and `skylence_edit` MCP tools are available (sky MCP server connected), use them to write and edit the workflow file. Never use the standard Write/Edit tools when the sky MCP server is connected. `skylence_read` returns a `В¶path#TAG` header; pass it verbatim in `skylence_edit` patches.

MCP server rule: for any node in the generated workflow whose task requires an external tool (Cartographer graph queries, GitHub API, Slack, Linear, or any other MCP-backed capability), include an `mcp_servers` key in that node's В§В§ config block with the relevant server(s). A `claude` node that calls Cartographer must declare the cartographer MCP server; a node posting to Slack must declare the Slack MCP server. Omit `mcp_servers` only when no node needs an external tool. Transport choice (see the skill's MCP section): prefer the built-in `skylence_*` tools when they cover the task (no server needed); for an external server hit by several or parallel nodes use a shared `http` daemon (`type:"http"`, `url`); use `stdio` (`command`/`args`) only for a single-node one-off, since it spawns a subprocess per node. Never use `sse` (deprecated).

Write the file вҖ” do not lint it yet.

Optional вҖ” add a `ui` key to one representative node (e.g. the first Claude prompt node) to demonstrate the dashboard card feature. When you include it, also create the companion markdown file at `{{dir}}/{{name}}/ui/<step>.en.md` (locale form) with YAML frontmatter:

```markdown
---
short_description: One-line summary shown on the node card.
long_description: Longer description shown when the card is expanded.
---
Brief markdown body describing what this step does, visible in the dashboard.
```

Wire it in the node config as `ui = "ui/<step>"` (extensionless, locale set). If the brief does not suggest any node that benefits from a card description, omit the `ui` key entirely вҖ” do not add it for its own sake.

Also add a workflow-level `ui = "ui/workflow"` key to the `вҠ•metaвҠ•` block (always include this), and create `{{dir}}/{{name}}/ui/workflow.en.md` with:

```markdown
---
short_description: One-line вҖ” what the workflow does.
long_description: The problem it solves and why it came to be.
changelog:
  - version: "1.0.0"
    date: "{{today}}"
    note: "Initial release."
---
Brief markdown body giving a human-readable overview of the workflow.
```

The `changelog` list supports `version` (required), `date` (optional, ISO 8601), and `note` (required). Include at least one entry.
вҲҶвҲҶ

вҖ»lintвҖ»
Step 2 вҖ” lint & fix. Loop node (max 6 passes) that reads {{dir}}/{{name}}/workflow.sky,
runs skyway lint, and fixes all errors. Edge: depends_on=["author"], trigger_rule=all_done.
Condition: loop.until.bash exits 0 (clean lint) or loop.max exhausted.
вҖ»вҖ»

В§lintВ§
model = "sonnet"
depends_on = ["author"]
skills = ["sky-workflow-authoring"]
loop.until.bash = "skyway lint \"$SKY_DIR/$SKY_NAME/workflow.sky\""
loop.max = 6
В§В§

вҲҶlintвҲҶ
Read {{dir}}/{{name}}/workflow.sky, then run `skyway lint {{dir}}/{{name}}/workflow.sky` and read its output. Fix every reported error and warning in the file, using the sky-workflow-authoring skill's error-code table (SKY-WF-*) to map each code to its fix. Common ones: quote the RHS of `when`; add `chain_from` targets to `depends_on`; quote `$SKY_*` in bash; declare every env-var reference in the `secrets` array. SKY-WF-103 (warning): `ui` key points to a markdown file that does not exist (applies to both the workflow-level `ui` in `вҠ•metaвҠ•` and per-node `ui` keys); create the missing file(s) at the declared path(s), or remove the key. Keep the workflow body in English. Re-run lint after editing. This node loops until lint passes; make concrete fixes each pass. When clean, output the final lint result and the file path.

File editing rule: if `skylence_read` and `skylence_edit` MCP tools are available (sky MCP server connected), use them for all reads and edits of the workflow file. Never use the standard Read/Edit/Write tools when the sky MCP server is connected.
вҲҶвҲҶ
